<tr id="L125"><td><a href="#L125">125</a></td><td>KIRK:  My what?</td></tr>

<tr id="L126"><td><a href="#L126">126</a></td><td>KOR:  The stupid, idiotic smile everyone else seems to be wearing. A Vulcan. Do you also have a tongue?</td></tr>

<tr id="L127"><td><a href="#L127">127</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I am Spock, a dealer in kevas and trillium.</td></tr>

<tr id="L128"><td><a href="#L128">128</a></td><td>KOS:  You do not look like a storekeeper. Take this man. Vulcans are members of the Federation. He may be a spy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L129"><td><a href="#L129">129</a></td><td>KIRK:  He's no spy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L130"><td><a href="#L130">130</a></td><td>KOR:  Well, have we a ram among the sheep? Do you object to us taking him?</td></tr>

<tr id="L131"><td><a href="#L131">131</a></td><td>KIRK:  He's done nothing. Nothing at all.</td></tr>

<tr id="L132"><td><a href="#L132">132</a></td><td>KOR:  Coming from an Organian, yours is practically an act of rebellion. Very good. (to the Council) So you welcome me. (to Kirk) Do you also welcome me?</td></tr>

<tr id="L133"><td><a href="#L133">133</a></td><td>KIRK:  You're here. There's nothing I can do about it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L134"><td><a href="#L134">134</a></td><td>KOR:  Good honest hatred. Very refreshing. However, it makes no difference whether you welcome me or not. I am here and will stay. You are now subjects of the Klingon Empire. You'll find there are many rules and regulations. They will be posted. Violation of the smallest of them will be punished by death.</td></tr>

<tr id="L135"><td><a href="#L135">135</a></td><td>AYELBORNE:  We shall obey your regulations, Commander.</td></tr>

<tr id="L136"><td><a href="#L136">136</a></td><td>KOR:  You disapprove, Baroner.</td></tr>

<tr id="L137"><td><a href="#L137">137</a></td><td>KIRK:  You need my approval?</td></tr>

<tr id="L138"><td><a href="#L138">138</a></td><td>KOR:  I need your obedience. Nothing more. Will I have it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L139"><td><a href="#L139">139</a></td><td>KIRK:  You seem to be in command.</td></tr>

<tr id="L140"><td><a href="#L140">140</a></td><td>KOR:  Yes. I am. I shall need a representative from among you. Liaison between the forces of the occupation and the civil population. Smile and smile. I don't trust men who smile too much. You, Baroner, you're the man.</td></tr>

<tr id="L141"><td><a href="#L141">141</a></td><td>KIRK:  Me? I don't want the job.</td></tr>

<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>KOR:  Have I asked whether or not you want it? We Klingons have a reputation for ruthlessness. You will find that it is deserved. Should one Klingon soldier be killed, a thousand Organians will die. I will have order. Is that clear?</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>AYELBORNE:  Commander, I assure you our people want nothing but peace. We shall cause you no trouble.</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>KOR:  I'm sure you will not. Take the Vulcan to the examination room. (to Kirk) You, come with me. I will familiarise you with your new duties.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>KIRK:  And Mister Spock?</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>KOR:  You are concerned?</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>KIRK:  He is my friend.</td></tr>

